phase2.explanation:
🤖 **Never call methods on nullable types without checking.**

**The problem:**
```kotlin
val text: String? = null
val length = text.length  // ❌ Compile error
```

**The fixes:**
```kotlin
// Fix 1: Safe call
val length = text?.length  // Returns null

// Fix 2: Elvis
val length = text?.length ?: 0  // Returns 0

// Fix 3: Check first
if (text != null) {
    val length = text.length  // Smart-cast to non-null
}

// Fix 4: Let
text?.let {
    val length = it.length  // Only runs if not null
}
```

**Kotlin-chan says:**
"Safe call. Elvis. Check. Never call directly on nullable types."

**Smart casting:**
```kotlin
if (text != null) {
    // text is smart-cast to String
    println(text.length)  // ✅ Works
}
```

phase3.solution:
fun getLength(text: String?): Int = text?.length ?: 0

fun main() {
    println(getLength("Hello"))  // 5
    println(getLength(null))     // 0
}
